### LookupValues API Test File

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001/api
@token = <insert_jwt_token_here>

### 1. Get all lookup values
GET {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 2. Create a new lookup value
POST {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lookupType": "Department",
  "value": "Information Technology",
  "code": "IT",
  "sortOrder": 1,
  "isActive": true
}

### 3. Create a child lookup value
POST {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lookupType": "Department",
  "value": "Software Development",
  "code": "SOFTDEV",
  "parentId": 1,
  "sortOrder": 1,
  "isActive": true
}

### 4. Get lookup value by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Get lookup values by type
GET {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues/type/Department
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Get active lookup values by type
GET {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues/type/Department/active
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Get children of a parent lookup
GET {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues/parent/1/children
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Update a lookup value
PUT {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lookupType": "Department",
  "value": "Information Technology Updated",
  "code": "IT",
  "sortOrder": 1,
  "isActive": true
}

### 9. Delete a lookup value
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/lookupvalues/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

